Project Title
Campus Book Lending System (CBLS)
CBLS is a command-line Python application that allows students to borrow and return books while tracking availability.

Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC)
1. Requirements Analysis
Functional Requirements:
Add new books to the system
View all books
Borrow books
Return books
Non-Functional Requirements:
Command-line interface
Written in Python 3.x
Data stored in memory (dictionary)
2. System Design
Architecture:
Single-file procedural Python program
Data Design:
books = {
"book_id": {
"title": str,
"author": str,
"available": bool
}
}
3. Implementation
File: cbls.py
Implements functions: add_book, view_books, borrow_book, return_book
CLI main menu to interact with system
4. Testing
Add multiple books
Borrow available book
Borrow unavailable book
Return borrowed book
Attempt invalid return
5. Deployment
Repository: sen201-cbls-project on GitHub
Run program via:
python cbls.py
6. Maintenance
Future improvements:
Persistent storage (file/database)
User authentication
Graphical interface

